# Auth Module Rules

## Endpoint Map (auth.py)
```
POST /auth/validate              ← NextAuth credentials authorize() pre-check
POST /auth/login                 ← JSON login → access + refresh tokens
POST /auth/token                 ← OAuth2 form login (Swagger UI)
POST /auth/refresh               ← Swap refresh token → new access token
POST /auth/register/contributor  ← 4-step contributor registration
POST /auth/register/enterprise   ← 4-step enterprise admin registration
POST /auth/sso/onboard           ← First-time SSO contributor profile creation
POST /auth/otp/send              ← Send phone or email OTP
POST /auth/otp/verify            ← Verify OTP
POST /auth/mfa/setup             ← Initiate TOTP provisioning
POST /auth/mfa/verify            ← Verify TOTP code
POST /auth/forgot-password       ← Send password-reset email
POST /auth/reset-password        ← Consume reset token + set new password
GET  /auth/me                    ← Current user profile (Bearer)
GET  /auth/users                 ← List users for approver dropdowns
```

## Token Pattern
- Access tokens: short-lived (ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES), type="access"
- Refresh tokens: 7 days, type="refresh"
- Always check `payload.get("type") == "access"` before trusting an access token
- Build token payloads with `{"sub": user_id, "role": role}`

## Password Reset Flow
1. `POST /auth/forgot-password` → generate token via `secrets.token_urlsafe(32)`, store in `password_resets` collection with TTL
2. `POST /auth/reset-password` → look up token, verify not expired, hash new password, delete token

## OTP Service (otp_service.py)
- `OTP_DRY_RUN=True` in dev → log OTP instead of sending
- OTP codes stored in `otp_codes` collection with TTL index on `expires_at`
- Expire after `OTP_EXPIRE_MINUTES` (default 10)
- Always invalidate OTP after successful verify

## Security Utilities (security.py)
- `get_password_hash(password)` → bcrypt via passlib
- `verify_password(plain, hashed)` → bcrypt verify
- `create_access_token(data, expires_delta)` → JWT
- `create_refresh_token(data)` → JWT with 7-day expiry
- `decode_token(token)` → raises 401 HTTPException on invalid/expired
- `get_current_user(token)` → FastAPI Depends, returns full user dict with `id` as string

## MongoDB Collections (auth)
- `users` — unique index on `email`
- `otp_codes` — compound index on (type, target) + TTL on expires_at
- `password_resets` — unique index on `token` + TTL on expires_at

## User Roles
From `UserRole` enum in `app/schemas/auth.py`:
- `enterprise_admin`
- `contributor`
- `viewer`
(always check role before performing admin operations)

## Never
- Never store plain-text passwords
- Never return password_hash in any response
- Never skip token type check (`type == "access"`) on protected routes
- Never reuse OTP after it's been verified
